com.ibm.mqlight.api

Interface JsonDelivery


  • public interface JsonDelivery
    A sub-type of delivery that is used to represent JSON data being received by the client.

    • Method Detail

      • getData

        <T> T getData(Class<T> classOfT)
          throws com.google.gson.JsonSyntaxException
        Deserializes the JSON data into an object of the specified class. Use the getData(Type) method instead if the class is of a generic type. This is equivalent to calling Gson.fromJson(String, Type).
        Parameters:
        classOfT - the class for the desired object.
        Returns:
        an object of type T (or null if the JSON is a representation of null).
        Throws:
        com.google.gson.JsonSyntaxException - if the JSON data cannot be deserialized into an object of type classOfT.

      • getData

        <T> T getData(Type typeOfT)
          throws com.google.gson.JsonSyntaxException
        Deserializes the JSON data into an object of the specified type. Use the getData(Class) method instead if the class is not of a generic type. This is equivalent to calling Gson.fromJson(String, Type).
        Parameters:
        typeOfT - the type for the desired object.
        Returns:
        an object of type T (or null if the JSON is a representation of null).
        Throws:
        com.google.gson.JsonSyntaxException - if the JSON data cannot be deserialized into an object of type typeOfT.

      • getData

        com.google.gson.JsonElement getData()
                                    throws com.google.gson.JsonParseException,
                                           com.google.gson.JsonSyntaxException
        Returns:
        a JsonElement representing the deserialized JSON data. This is equivalent to calling JsonParser.parse(String).
        Throws:
        com.google.gson.JsonParseException - if the data is not valid JSON.
        com.google.gson.JsonSyntaxException - if the data contains malformed JSON elements.

      • getRawData

        String getRawData()
        Returns:
        a String representation of the JSON. This allows other parsers to be used.
